{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "go-enterprise-api-collection",
		"name": "Go Enterprise API",
		"description": "Complete API collection for Go Enterprise API project.\n\n## Getting Started\n\n1. Import this collection into Postman\n2. Import the environment file (Go_Enterprise_API.postman_environment.json)\n3. Start the server: `go run cmd/api/main.go`\n4. Register a user first, then login to get tokens\n5. The collection will automatically use the access token for protected routes\n\n## Authentication Flow\n\n1. Register → Creates new user and returns tokens\n2. Login → Returns access_token and refresh_token\n3. Use access_token in Authorization header\n4. When token expires, use refresh endpoint",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
	"variable": [
		{
			"key": "baseUrl",
			"value": "http://localhost:8080/api/v1",
			"type": "string"
		}
	],
	"auth": {
		"type": "bearer",
		"bearer": [
			{
				"key": "token",
				"value": "{{access_token}}",
				"type": "string"
			}
		]
	},
